column5: Tha calm B4 The Storm. Headed out to my spot close to Innisfil Beach. Got set-up with Tarpus Minimus by 10:40 A.M. Had A North by North East Wind.. only about 5-10 Km / hour, so it wasn't too bad. After about 20 minutes and one small Perch, decided to move shallower, walked about 40 feet, and drilled my second hole. 3 Perch later and another 20 minutes decided to move a little shallower by walking another 15 paces. Drilled my third hole, and within 2 minutes caught another Perch, then nothing for 15 minutes.  Walked another 20 paces drilled my 4th hole, and this was the spot, as I caught one after another.  I was also rewarded with a nice sized Whitefish, which I guesstimate to be around 5lbs.  About 1/2 hour b4 leaving I received some unexpected company, some hopefull anglers who decided to fish in my holes I had cut earlier.  B4 I left I advised the lady to fish in my productive hole, and she immediately began getting hits.   Here is the catch...
Nice catch Jed will you and Granny be eating those critters with some possum inners and some grits.  Whats this no shots of Tarpus!!!!!!!!!!!
I'm with Mike the Pike, where's the Minimus shot!  Nice whitefish btw
Nice Haul that one perch at the top looks pretty huge
Gotta love those fry up morsels Clampet. Nice catch guy!
Nice to see that you are still having luck out there!   Bly
Nice job Clampet - suppose to be gusts to 70km during this upcoming storm tommorow - maybe you should give Tarpus a good test
WELL DONE THERE BUD.....thats a nice haul of simcoes finest..  ....someone get the frying pan ready,time for diner....cheers
Good shooting Jed.  I'll give 'er another shot this weekend.
Nice pics and report as always Clampet.
Great pics and report Clampet..... you make Jethro proud!  Nice to see you putting the new Normark "Micro-drill" to work..... moving around is the key to success!....Great Job... Greg.
Very nice!  What did the whitefish snack on for it's last meal?  Tony
70Km wind, never mind your tarpus flatus, I think there may be the odd huttus rollus.  Nice catch BTW.
Nice whitefish and not a bad haul with the perch, good job...
very nice where were all the fish when the tyler derby was on??????????lol
Quite the haul. Excellent report and pics. Thanks!  Cheers, 1leg
